The case against the leader of the Economic Freedom Fighters, Julius Malema and MP Mbuyiseni Ndlozi returns to the Randburg Magistrates Court. #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - EFF (Economic Freedom Fighters) leader Julius Malema and party MP Mbuyiseni Ndlozi, will return to the Randburg Magistrate's Court on Wednesday. The pair are charged with the alleged assaulting of a police officer at the funeral of Winnie Madikizela-Mandela in 2018. READ:Â Malema accuses some Senekal farmers of intimidation The incident was caught on CCTV and released by AfriForum last year. During their last court appearance, Malema told journalists the charges are a waste of time and should be scrapped.